                android:id="@+id/textView18"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="1. Prepare the Shrimp:

Pat the shrimp dry with paper towels and season with salt and black pepper.
2. Cook the Pasta:

Cook the linguine or spaghetti according to the package instructions until al dente. Reserve about 1 cup of pasta cooking water, then drain.
3. Cook the Shrimp:

In a large skillet, heat 2 tablespoons of butter and 2 tablespoons of olive oil over medium-high heat.

Add the seasoned shrimp to the skillet and cook for 1-2 minutes on each side or until they just turn pink. Be careful not to overcook the shrimp. Remove the shrimp from the skillet and set aside.

4. Make the Scampi Sauce:

In the same skillet, add the remaining 2 tablespoons of butter and 2 tablespoons of olive oil.

Add minced garlic and red pepper flakes. Sauté for about 1 minute until the garlic becomes fragrant, being careful not to brown it.

Pour in the white wine and let it simmer for 2-3 minutes to reduce slightly.

Add the cooked shrimp back to the skillet and toss to coat them in the sauce.

Squeeze the juice of one lemon into the skillet and toss again.

5. Combine Shrimp with Pasta:

Add the drained pasta to the skillet, tossing it with the shrimp and sauce until well combined.

If needed, add some of the reserved pasta cooking water to loosen the sauce.

6. Garnish and Serve:

Sprinkle fresh chopped parsley over the shrimp scampi and toss.

Optionally, serve with grated Parmesan cheese on the side.

Serve immediately, and enjoy your delicious Shrimp Scampi!"
